channel.title: Mislabeled RST pads next for headphone jack?
channel.description:
I just noticed that the silk-screen labelling for the solder-pads of the headphone jack where in a different order than the ones on the other pads (R-S-T vs.. S-T-R). I checked with a multimeter and I am quite sure they are mixed up and should be _just like the others_. If someone could please confirm this, I'd be more than happy :smile:
(Axoloti core v1.0)

item.title: Mislabeled RST pads next for headphone jack?
item.dc:creator: @johannes johannes
item.description:
@johannes wrote:

I can confirm they are mislabeled, however it is the T(ip) and R(ing) that are swapped, so still in a different order than the quarter inch jacks.
This affects both Axoloti Core revision v1.0 and v1.1.

In practice this is just the left and right channel swapped in only the silkscreen labels.
